.Cryptic numbers, problem statement. You are given two integers, L and R, representing the target range of numbers inclusive. A number is called a cryptic number if it satisfies all the following conditions. First, it is divisible by seven. Second, it is not divisible by five. Third, it is not a palindrome. Fourth, it does not contain any repeated digits. Your task is to print all cryptic numbers in the given range. If no such number exists, print minus one